Greenearth Energy Plans to Raise $3.7 Million From New Shares

-- B y   B a l d a v e   S i n g h
-- 
2011-09-15T00:15:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/greenearth-energy-plans-to-raise-3-7-million-from-new-shares.html
Greenearth Energy Ltd. (GER)  plans to
raise as much as AUD 3.6 million ($3.7 million) from a rights
issue to fund renewable energy projects, the company said in a
statement.  The non-renounceable 1 for 2 rights issue will be priced at
AUD 8 cents per new share, Greenearth said. Shareholders who
subscribe will also receive 1 non-listed option for every new
share they subscribe at no cost, exercisable at AUD 5 cents
each.  It will issue as much as 45 million new shares, the
proceeds of which will be used to fund solar, geothermal and
biomass projects, Greenearth said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Baldave Singh at 
 bsingh35@bloomberg.net  